suppressions.reason:
Some of the AWS protocols make use of deprecated traits, and some are
themselves deprecated traits. As this package is intended to test those
protocols, the warnings should be suppressed.

These shapes are intended to be used to validate vendorParams in
protocol tests, so they naturally will not be connected to a service.

smithy.api#enum.name: CLIENT
smithy.api#enum.documentation: The test only applies to client implementations.

smithy.api#enum.name: SERVER
smithy.api#enum.documentation: The test only applies to server implementations.

smithy.api#enum.name: FULL
smithy.api#enum.documentation:
Indicates that the CloudFormation property generated from this
member does not have any mutability restrictions, meaning that it
can be specified by the user and returned in a `read` or `list`
request.

smithy.api#enum.name: CREATE_AND_READ
smithy.api#enum.documentation:
Indicates that the CloudFormation property generated from this
member can be specified only during resource creation and can be
returned in a `read` or `list` request.

smithy.api#enum.name: CREATE
smithy.api#enum.documentation:
Indicates that the CloudFormation property generated from this
member can be specified only during resource creation and cannot
be returned in a `read` or `list` request. MUST NOT be set if the
member is also marked with the `@additionalIdentifier` trait.

smithy.api#enum.name: READ
smithy.api#enum.documentation:
Indicates that the CloudFormation property generated from this
member can be returned by a `read` or `list` request, but
cannot be set by the user.

smithy.api#enum.name: WRITE
smithy.api#enum.documentation:
Indicates that the CloudFormation property generated from this
member can be specified by the user, but cannot be returned by a
`read` or `list` request. MUST NOT be set if the member is also
marked with the `@additionalIdentifier` trait.

smithy.api#enum.name: CUSTOMER_CONTENT
smithy.api#enum.documentation: Customer content means any software (including machine images), data, text, audio, video or images that customers or any customer end user transfers to AWS for processing, storage or hosting by AWS services in connection with the customer?s accounts and any computational results that customers or any customer end user derive from the foregoing through their use of AWS services.

smithy.api#enum.name: CUSTOMER_ACCOUNT_INFORMATION
smithy.api#enum.documentation: Account information means information about customers that customers provide to AWS in connection with the creation or administration of customers? accounts.

smithy.api#enum.name: SERVICE_ATTRIBUTES
smithy.api#enum.documentation: Service Attributes means service usage data related to a customer?s account, such as resource identifiers, metadata tags, security and access roles, rules, usage policies, permissions, usage statistics, logging data, and analytics.

smithy.api#enum.documentation: Designates metadata tags applied to AWS resources.

smithy.api#enum.name: PERMISSIONS_DATA
